<TITLE> SSC, equivalent exams put off to March 27 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 18 (bdnews24.com)The SSC and Dakhil examinations of 2008 have been deferred for one month, the government said in a statement Tuesday. The examinations will now begin on March 27, according to the new schedule. The government took the decision, taking into account the difficulties of the students in southern and southwestern areas ravaged by the Nov 15 cyclone, the statement said. The examinations had earlier been scheduled to begin on Feb 27. Other examinations equivalent to Secondary School Certificate examinations will also begin the same day, the Press Information Department said in the statement. bd
